DURBAN, August 15 – KwaZulu-Natal police have arrested three suspects for allegedly operating a hydroponic dagga laboratory at Ellingham Estate Farm. The suspects, aged between 25 and 45, were allegedly dealing in cannabis plants and oil. Police spokesperson Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo said a multi-disciplinary team, comprising of the Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation (Hawks), Crime Intelligence and the Tactical Response Team, swooped on the lab earlier this week. Cannabis plants, oil and equipment worth about half a million rand, were confiscated. The suspects are expected to appear at the Umzito Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday. – African News Agency (ANA)